VALUES
(43, 3, 32, 45, 10, 16, 21, 'no man receiveth his testimony', 'Testimony and Obedience Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of testimony and belief. John 3:32 mentions the lack of reception of testimony, while Romans 10:16 addresses disobedience to the gospel despite hearing it.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 32, 45, 11, 2, 6, 'no man receiveth his testimony', 'Testimony and Remnant Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of testimony and reception. In John, the lack of acceptance of testimony parallels the remnant in Romans, who remain faithful despite widespread rejection. Both passages emphasize the idea of a select group acknowledging truth amidst disbelief.', 'theme', 0.3, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 33, 49, 1, 13, 13, 'set to his seal that God is true', 'Sealing and Truth Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of being sealed as a sign of truth. Both passages emphasize the act of receiving testimony and believing, which leads to being sealed, affirming God''s truth.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 33, 58, 6, 17, 17, 'God is true', 'God''s Truth and Immutability', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s truthfulness and reliability. Both passages emphasize the assurance that God is true and that His promises are immutable, as confirmed by His oath.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 33, 47, 1, 18, 18, 'God is true', 'Truthfulness of God', 'Both passages emphasize the truthfulness of God. John 3:33 states that God is true, while 2 Corinthians 1:18 affirms this truth in relation to the speaker''s message.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 33, 56, 1, 1, 2, 'God is true', 'Truth and God''s Promises', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of truth, with John affirming that God is true and Titus highlighting the acknowledgment of truth that leads to godliness. Additionally, Titus mentions God''s promise of eternal life, reinforcing the reliability of God''s word, which aligns with the affirmation of truth in John.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 33, 43, 6, 27, 27, 'God is true', 'Connection of Sealing and Testimony', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s truth and the sealing of His chosen. Both passages emphasize the importance of receiving God''s testimony and the sealing of the Son of man by God.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 33, 45, 3, 3, 4, 'God is true', 'Truth and Belief Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of God''s truthfulness in contrast to human unbelief. John 3:33 asserts that those who accept God''s testimony affirm His truth, while Romans 3:4 states that God is true despite human doubt.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 33, 45, 4, 18, 21, 'God is true', 'Faith and God''s Promises', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief in God''s truth and promises. Both passages emphasize the importance of faith in God''s ability to fulfill His word, as seen in the assurance of God''s truth in John and Abraham''s unwavering faith in Romans.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 34, 44, 10, 38, 38, 'for God giveth not the Spirit by measure unto him', 'Connection of Divine Anointing', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Holy Spirit in Jesus'' ministry. John 3:34 states that God gives the Spirit without measure to Jesus, while Acts 10:38 describes His anointing with the Holy Ghost and power.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 34, 40, 12, 18, 18, 'God giveth not the Spirit by measure', 'Connection of Divine Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the giving of God''s Spirit. John 3:34 states that God gives the Spirit without measure, while Matthew 12:18 mentions putting the Spirit upon His chosen servant.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 34, 43, 15, 26, 26, 'God giveth not the Spirit by measure', 'Connection of the Spirit''s Role', 'This connection highlights the role of the Spirit in both passages. John 3:34 emphasizes that God gives the Spirit without measure to the one He sends, while John 15:26 describes the Spirit of truth sent from the Father to testify of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 34, 43, 5, 26, 26, 'for God giveth not the Spirit by measure unto him', 'Connection of Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the divine authority given to the Son. John 3:34 highlights that God gives the Spirit without measure, while John 5:26 states that the Father has given life to the Son, indicating a shared divine nature.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 34, 23, 11, 2, 5, 'for God giveth not the Spirit by measure unto him', 'Connection of the Spirit''s Role', 'Both passages emphasize the Spirit''s role in empowering the one sent by God. John 3:34 highlights that God gives the Spirit without measure, while Isaiah 11:2 describes the Spirit resting upon the coming figure, endowing him with wisdom and understanding.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 34, 51, 2, 9, 9, 'for God giveth not the Spirit by measure unto him', 'Connection of Divine Fulness', 'This connection highlights the divine authority and presence of Jesus. Both passages emphasize that he is filled with God''s Spirit and embodies the fullness of the Godhead.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 34, 42, 4, 18, 18, 'God giveth not the Spirit by measure unto him', 'Connection of the Spirit''s Role', 'This connection highlights the role of the Spirit in empowering Jesus for His mission. Both passages emphasize that Jesus speaks God''s words and is anointed to bring healing and deliverance.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 35, 40, 28, 18, 18, 'all things into his hand', 'Authority of Jesus', 'This connection highlights the theme of authority given to Jesus. Both passages emphasize that all things and power are entrusted to Him by the Father.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 35, 43, 5, 20, 20, 'The Father loveth the Son', 'Connection of Divine Love', 'Both passages emphasize the love of the Father for the Son, highlighting the intimate relationship between them. Additionally, they both mention the Father revealing things to the Son, indicating a shared knowledge and authority.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 35, 42, 10, 22, 22, 'all things into his hand', 'Connection of Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the authority given by the Father to the Son. John 3:35 states that the Father has given all things into the Son''s hand, while Luke 10:22 reiterates that all things are delivered to the Son by the Father.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 35, 40, 11, 27, 27, 'all things into his hand', 'Divine Authority of the Son', 'Both passages emphasize the authority given to the Son by the Father. John 3:35 states that ''all things'' are in the Son''s hand, while Matthew 11:27 affirms that ''all things are delivered unto me of my Father.''', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 35, 43, 17, 2, 2, 'given all things into his hand', 'Authority of the Son', 'Both passages emphasize the authority given to the Son. In John 3:35, it states that the Father has given all things into his hand, while John 17:2 highlights that he has power over all flesh.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 35, 19, 2, 8, 8, 'given all things into his hand', 'Inheritance and Authority Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of inheritance and authority given by God. In John 3:35, the Father gives all things into the Son''s hand, while Psalms 2:8 speaks of God granting the heathen as an inheritance to the Son.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 35, 23, 9, 6, 7, NULL, 'Connection of Authority and Sonship', 'This connection highlights the authority given to the Son in John 3:35 and the prophetic declaration of a son given in Isaiah 9:6. Both passages emphasize the significance of the Son''s role in governance and divine authority.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 36, 43, 5, 24, 24, 'everlasting life', 'Connection of Everlasting Life', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''everlasting life'' for those who believe. They also highlight the consequences of disbelief, indicating a separation from life and the presence of condemnation or wrath.', 'theme', 0.6779999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 36, 43, 1, 12, 12, NULL, 'Belief and Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of belief in Jesus for receiving eternal life and becoming a child of God. The connection highlights that belief is central to both the promise of everlasting life and the empowerment to become sons of God.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 36, 52, 5, 9, 9, 'the wrath of God abideth on him', 'Connection of Wrath and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between wrath and salvation. John 3:36 states that the wrath of God abides on those who do not believe in the Son, while 1 Thessalonians 5:9 affirms that God has not appointed believers to wrath but to salvation.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 36, 49, 5, 6, 6, 'the wrath of God', 'Connection of God''s Wrath', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of God''s wrath directed towards those who do not believe or are disobedient. John 3:36 states that ''the wrath of God abideth on him'' who does not believe in the Son, while Ephesians 5:6 mentions that ''the wrath of God'' comes upon ''the children of disobedience.''', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 36, 62, 5, 10, 13, 'hath everlasting life', 'Eternal Life in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize that belief in the Son leads to eternal life. They also highlight the consequences of not believing, which is the absence of life. This connection underscores the importance of faith in Jesus for salvation.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 36, 45, 1, 17, 18, 'the wrath of God abideth on him', 'Connection of Faith and Wrath', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of belief and disbelief. John 3:36 speaks of the wrath of God abiding on those who do not believe in the Son, while Romans 1:18 reveals God''s wrath against unrighteousness, linking faith to the avoidance of divine wrath.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 36, 45, 5, 9, 9, 'the wrath of God abideth on him', 'Connection of Wrath and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of wrath associated with unbelief and the promise of salvation through belief in the Son. John 3:36 warns that ''the wrath of God abideth on him'' for those who do not believe, while Romans 5:9 assures that believers are ''saved from wrath through him.''', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
